Module iu.util.logging
Package edu.iu.logging

Interface IuLogContext

public interface IuLogContext
Provides thread-bound context information for log events.

  • Method Details

    • initializeContext

      static void initializeContext(String endpoint, String application, String environment)
      Binds top-level attributes to log events observed in the current thread's context.

      This method SHOULD be invoked exactly once during initialization, typically once per container, to bind per-ClassLoader node-level runtime attributes.

      Parameters:
      endpoint - endpoint identifier
      application - application code
      environment - environment code

    • follow

      static <T> T follow(IuLogContext context, String message, UnsafeSupplier<T> supplier) throws Throwable
      Applies full context attributes to log events generated during the invocation of an application-defined UnsafeSupplier.
      Type Parameters:
      T - return type
      Parameters:
      context - IuLogContext
      message - short message to augment trace behavior
      supplier - processing task to follow
      Returns:
      value from UnsafeSupplier.get()
      Throws:
      Throwable - from UnsafeSupplier.get()
